Sorry to dig up an old thread, but I wanted to mention that you can embed a directx window into your windows form.  Then you can just draw directly to a Texture2D.  That is what I'm doing with my emulator. And though some examples mention it, it is not necessary to use multiple threads to accomplish this.<br /><br />Here is just one example: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gosub.com/OpenSource/DirectXControl/DirectXControl.htm">http://gosub.com/OpenSource/DirectXCont ... ontrol.htm</a><!-- m --><br /><br />You can find a few others if you google a bit for them.<br /><br />I hope this information might be somewhat helpful if anyone is doing a search later on.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4449">tineras</a> — Fri Jul 16, 2010 2:33 pm</p><hr />
